					 <p>Maintaining an ideal body temperature is required when it comes to keeping patients warm during the surgery period. In order to provide the best service to patients, read out important things about patient warming systems. Wallabies Warm Care in Ontario, Canada is the leading supplier of these medical devices. </p>
<h1>Maintains body temperature</h1>
<p>The core human body temperature is close to 37 degrees Celsius. Hypothermia is referred to a body temperature that is below 36 degrees. The difference in body temperature is maintained through thermoregulation. Patient warmers work to maintain a core body temperature that prevents patients from hypothermic conditions. </p>
